            <trans-unit id="">
                <source>Sub-language deduction: This value is subtracted from the language resource’s match rate for the analysis IF the sub-language of the task differs from the sub-language of the language resource.↵<br/><br/>Examples:<br/>↵ – Source language task: de-AT, language resource: de-DE =&gt; The deduction is applied.<br/>↵ – Target language task: en-US, language resource: en-GB =&gt; The deduction is applied.<br/>↵ – Source language task: de-AT, language resource: de =&gt; The deduction is NOT applied.<br/>↵ – Target language task: de, language resource: de-DE =&gt; The deduction is NOT applied.<br/>↵<br/>↵When the deduction is applied, read/write access to the TM is reduced to read access (this can be changed manually per task).</source>
                <target>Sub-language deduction: This value is subtracted from the language resource’s match rate for the analysis IF the sub-language of the task differs from the sub-language of the language resource.↵<br/><br/>Examples:<br/>↵ – Source language task: de-AT, language resource: de-DE =&gt; The deduction is applied.<br/>↵ – Target language task: en-US, language resource: en-GB =&gt; The deduction is applied.<br/>↵ – Source language task: de-AT, language resource: de =&gt; The deduction is NOT applied.<br/>↵ – Target language task: de, language resource: de-DE =&gt; The deduction is NOT applied.<br/>↵<br/>↵When the deduction is applied, read/write access to the TM is reduced to read access (this can be changed manually per task).</target>
            </trans-unit>
