                <source>Terms in the TBX will always be merged first by ID with existing entries in the TermCollection. If “Merge terms” is checked and the ID in the TBX is not found in the TermCollection, it will be checked whether the same term already exists in the same language. If yes, the entire term entries will be merged. Especially with a TermCollection with many languages, this may lead to unwanted results.</source>
                <target>Terms in the TBX will always be merged first by ID with existing entries in the TermCollection. If “Merge terms” is checked and the ID in the TBX is not found in the TermCollection, it will be checked whether the same term already exists in the same language. If yes, the entire term entries will be merged. Especially with a TermCollection with many languages, this may lead to unwanted results.</target>
            </trans-unit>
